==English==
===Noun===
'''pervert''' (''plural'' '''perverts''')

#One who has been perverted; one who has turned to [[error]], especially in [[religion]]; – opposed to [[convert]]. See the Synonym of Convert.
#:''Note'' In current usage, more frequently refers to [[sexual]] [[deviancy]] than to [[false]] [[religious]] [[belief]]s.

====Synonyms====
*[[deviant]], [[perv]]

===Translations===
*Chinese: [[堕落者]] (duò luò zhě)

====See Also====
*[[perverse]]
*[[perversion]]

===Verb (transitive)===
#To turnanother way; to divert.
#To turn from truth, rectitude, or propriety; to divert from a right use, end, or way; to lead astray; to corrupt; also, to misapply; to misinterpret designedly; as, to pervert one's words.

===Verb (intransitive)===
#To become perverted; to take the wrong course.